node.text:
After successfully battling cancer and years of being immersed behind the scenes as a songwriter, scoring a multitude of sync licensing placements for commercials and popular TV shows, @PJPacifico is stepping back to the front and with a new album, showing why the songs he writes, largely drawn from his own real-life experiences, are so relatable and universal. His new, heartfelt single #EveryLittleHeartbreak was inspired by the isolation that came from pandemic lockdown and was written/recorded with the help of his fabulous #songwriter friends @GarrisonStarr + @Valerie.Broussard. It’s the first single from his upcoming album, “What I Missed In The Mirror,” due out later this year. Plus, after such a long period of solitude and with #NYC loosening its restrictions, it feels great to slowly start over again... and "take the risk" as the song entails! So, make sure you listen to his new single because between its rich harmonies, powerful tones, and heartfelt lyrics, the only thing #PJPacifico will be behind from here on out will be his guitar, making hits! 🎸 

Follow @ViperRecords for more updates

Catch them at @boweryballroom ‪March 10‬ + more tour dates around the US and Canada @tcbpublicrelations #subwaycreatures

node.text: This afternoon in Union Square a man in a wheelchair somehow ended up on the subway tracks. Luckily, a Good Samaritan jumped down and rescued the man (and his wheelchair) about 10 seconds before the train came into the station. Huge shoutout to whoever the guy is who jumped down to help! #subwaycreatures
